41
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:34,044
JIMMY:
Oh, hey. Come on in.

42
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:36,255
Hi. I'm Francesca Liddy.

43
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:39,341
-I'm here for the interview.
-Oh. Jimmy McGill.

44
00:12:39,508 --> 00:12:41,802
Hey, are you running early,
or am I running late?

45
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:43,637
No, sorry. I'm a little early.

46
00:12:43,804 --> 00:12:46,307
It's not a problem.
Never bad to be early...

47
00:12:46,474 --> 00:12:48,767
...except in death and taxes...

48
00:12:48,934 --> 00:12:50,227
...and some other things.

49
00:12:50,394 --> 00:12:51,479
[LAUGHS]

50
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:54,356
-Hey, can I ask you a question?
-Sure.

51
00:12:54,523 --> 00:12:56,817
Does that look straight to you?

52
00:12:57,526 --> 00:12:58,694
Uh....

53
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:01,614
I think there-- That side--

54
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:04,617
I think you're a little crooked.

55
00:13:04,825 --> 00:13:06,869
The bottom of the "M" there.

56
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:12,917
Yeah. A little crooked.

57
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:17,588
So you're coming off
of seven years at the MVD?

58
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:19,757
-I am, yeah.
-Here's a question.

59
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:23,427
How come New Mexico doesn't call it
the DMV like every other state?

60
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:26,013
Well, that's a great question.

61
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,473
Just like in Arizona...

62
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,851
...the Motor Vehicles Division
is part of the DOT, a division.

63
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:33,270
Whereas, in most other states, the DMV...

64
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:36,023
...or Department of Motor Vehicles
is its own entity.

65
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:40,819
So I don't know if that answers the question,
except to say that's the government for you.

66
00:13:41,028 --> 00:13:44,949
You got that right. Well, I for one,
am not calling it the MVD.

67
00:13:45,115 --> 00:13:47,576
DMV all the way.

68
00:13:47,868 --> 00:13:50,496
What do you think you learned
the most working there?

69
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:52,665
Patience. Diplomacy.

70
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:55,501
You meet all sorts of people down there.

71
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:59,838
And most are really great, really friendly,
but you encounter some who are upset...

72
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:01,799
-...belligerent.
-What about old folks?

73
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:05,177
-You get your fair share of them?
-Oh, lots of elderly drivers.

74
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:09,139
After 75, they need to take their test again,
so if they don't pass...

75
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:12,893
...you have to explain why their license
isn't being renewed, which is hard.

76
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:14,853
What do you say then? Do you ever...

77
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:17,147
...yell at them? I mean, geezers, right?

78
00:14:17,314 --> 00:14:19,233
How can you not?

79
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:23,028
No, I would never. No.

80
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:25,656
Nor should you. That was a trick question.

81
00:14:25,823 --> 00:14:28,242
You passed with flying colors. Very good.

82
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:30,119
Heh, okay. Well, then...

83
00:14:30,286 --> 00:14:33,122
...so Jimmy and I have very different needs.

84
00:14:33,289 --> 00:14:37,293
His practice is mostly wills
for senior citizens...

85
00:14:37,459 --> 00:14:40,838
...while I'm focused on
a single client at the moment, Mesa Verde...

86
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:43,883
...with banking regulations
that generate a ton of paperwork.

87
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:47,344
So I'm looking for someone
with an eye for organization...

88
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:49,555
-...and detail.
-Well, DMV's great for that.

89
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:51,682
Tons of detail in those driver's licenses.

90
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:53,684
We did see hundreds of people every day.

91
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:56,937
And you'd never want to let a mistake
slip through on their forms.

92
00:14:57,104 --> 00:15:01,108
-You'd have a horrible cascade of problems.
-Sounds challenging.

93
00:15:01,275 --> 00:15:03,527
So why the law?

94
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:06,238
I mean, why leave the DMV or MVD?

95
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:09,533
I have to imagine you'll be giving up
a good benefits package.

96
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:12,286
Good health care and retirement plans...

97
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:15,372
...but there's a bureaucracy
to government work...

98
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:18,000
...that ultimately became too frustrating.

99
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,419
I guess what you'd call it,
too much red tape.

100
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:22,963
I just wanna be somewhere
I can make a difference.

101
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:25,466
That's us.
We're all about making a difference.

102
00:15:25,674 --> 00:15:28,427
And I see here both Word and Excel,
you're comfortable with?

103
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:30,137
-Absolutely.
-Excel and Word, wow!

104
00:15:30,304 --> 00:15:32,222
Well, you had me at old people.

105
00:15:32,389 --> 00:15:34,433
Hey, here's a question. Can you start today?

106
00:15:35,225 --> 00:15:36,518
-I....
-Can--

107
00:15:37,227 --> 00:15:38,896
-Yes?
-Fantastic.

108
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:42,316
Can you just give us a second, Francesca?

109
00:15:42,483 --> 00:15:46,153
Absolutely. I.... Of course. Um....

110
00:15:46,362 --> 00:15:48,614
-Thank you.
-Uh-huh.

111
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:54,995
What are you doing?

112
00:15:55,162 --> 00:15:56,580
What? I like her.

113
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:59,917
"Can you start today?"
Don't you think we should see more résumés...

114
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:01,168
...like, a lot more?

115
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:03,379
She is our first interview.

116
00:16:03,545 --> 00:16:06,173
-We haven't checked her references.
-So we'll check them.

117
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:09,218
Kim, you've been taking forever
searching for a paralegal.

118
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,011
