-Haven't found the right fit.

119
00:16:11,178 --> 00:16:13,430
Yeah, because you're searching
for perfection...

120
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:15,683
...and perfection is the enemy
of perfectly adequate.

121
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:18,394
-That's the bar? Adequate?
-She's more than adequate.

122
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:19,770
She worked at the DMV.

123
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:21,855
That's like the fifth circle of hell.

124
00:16:22,022 --> 00:16:24,650
Look, she's overqualified.
If it doesn't work out...

125
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:26,568
...we can fire her. It's no big deal.

126
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:29,989
Don't you think someone with
actual legal experience would be better?

127
00:16:30,197 --> 00:16:32,908
I've got a commercial airing in 11 minutes...

128
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:35,494
...so the phones are gonna be ringing.
I need help.

129
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,663
Can we give her a test run, please?

130
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:39,623
I got a good feeling about this.

131
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:43,210
Come on, Kim.

132
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:47,673
[SIGHS]

133
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:50,718
Now, getting these oldsters to call,
that's half the battle...

134
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:53,887
-...so they need to hear a friendly voice.
-Friendly? Absolutely.

135
00:16:54,054 --> 00:16:56,306
Speak loudly and clearly...

136
00:16:56,473 --> 00:17:00,185
...but be careful with the loud and clear
because it can come off as angry.

137
00:17:00,352 --> 00:17:01,562
Be folksy.

138
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:04,023
-Put a little sunshine in your voice.
-Got it.

139
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:07,526
Okay. You need coffee or water?
You need to hit the head before things--

140
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:08,777
[PHONE RINGING]

141
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:10,821
Oh. There it goes. Heh.

142
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:14,700
Offices of Jimmy McGill. How may I help you?

143
