242
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:36,581
WOMAN: Hi. Welcome to Los Pollos Hermanos.
Can I take your order?

243
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:39,751
Give me a number three. Potatoes, coffee.

244
00:23:40,627 --> 00:23:42,879
WOMAN:
Would you like bonus size for 50 cents more?

245
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:45,006
MAN 6: No.
WOMAN: Dining in or to go?

246
00:23:45,423 --> 00:23:46,758
In.

247
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:49,177
WOMAN: Will that be all? Four eighty-nine.
MAN 6: Yeah.

248
00:23:49,344 --> 00:23:52,180
MAN 5: When you get behind the eight ball....
MAN 8: I know. You're right.

249
00:23:53,557 --> 00:23:55,892
Yeah, no problem.

250
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:59,187
WOMAN: Do you need any extra salsa?
-Yeah. Give me that.

251
00:24:00,397 --> 00:24:01,940
[CLEARS THROAT]

252
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:13,410
MAN 9:
Here's a number three.

253
00:24:14,911 --> 00:24:16,913
WOMAN:
Here you go. Have a great day.

254
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:31,094
MAN 1:
Manuel, where's my 22?

255
00:24:32,053 --> 00:24:33,847
MANUEL:
Coming up.

256
00:25:13,511 --> 00:25:15,305
MAN 1:
Pick it up.

257
00:25:16,556 --> 00:25:20,018
WOMAN: Thank you for coming to Los Pollos
Hermanos. Have a great day now.

258
00:25:33,990 --> 00:25:35,700
Hi. Welcome to Los Pollos Hermanos.

259
00:26:41,308 --> 00:26:45,312
MAN 1: You ready or are you still looking?
MAN 10: Sorry. I'm still trying to decide.

260
00:26:45,478 --> 00:26:47,897
MAN 1:
Okay, just let me know when.

261
00:27:24,225 --> 00:27:25,935
MAN 11:
Can I help you?

262
00:27:28,688 --> 00:27:29,731
JIMMY:
Uh....

263
00:27:29,939 --> 00:27:33,443
My watch, uh, clasp is loose. It...

264
00:27:33,610 --> 00:27:36,738
-...falls. I tried to reach it. Heh.
-Oh.

265
00:27:36,946 --> 00:27:38,073
Well, I'm sorry.

266
00:27:38,239 --> 00:27:39,699
Allow me.

267
00:27:42,452 --> 00:27:45,830
You know, they say a nice watch band
is as important as the watch.

268
00:27:45,997 --> 00:27:48,166
That's what I get for cheaping out.

269
00:27:49,292 --> 00:27:50,960
We'll find it for you.

270
00:27:54,506 --> 00:27:55,757
Where the heck is it?

271
00:27:55,924 --> 00:27:58,760
Oh, don't worry. If it's in here, I'll-- Ah.

272
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:01,054
There it is.

273
00:28:03,556 --> 00:28:05,850
May I clean this for you?
We have alcohol wipes.

274
00:28:06,017 --> 00:28:08,269
No, it's been in worse places.

275
00:28:08,436 --> 00:28:10,647
Thank you. That was very nice of you.

276
00:28:10,814 --> 00:28:13,108
No problem. It's my pleasure.

277
00:28:13,358 --> 00:28:16,736
-Is there anything else I can do for you?
-Uh.... No.

278
00:28:16,903 --> 00:28:18,029
Thanks.

279
00:28:18,196 --> 00:28:19,864
You take care.

280
00:28:22,325 --> 00:28:23,785
MIKE: <i>Tell me again.</i>
JIMMY: <i>Jesus.</i>

281
00:28:23,952 --> 00:28:27,622
<i>-How many ways you want me to say it?</i>
MIKE: <i>Just tell me what you saw.</i>

282
00:28:27,789 --> 00:28:29,791
JIMMY:
<i>He came in, like you said he would.</i>

283
00:28:29,999 --> 00:28:34,254
He ordered the number three
with potatoes and coffee...

284
00:28:34,421 --> 00:28:36,089
...went bold with the extra salsa...

285
00:28:36,297 --> 00:28:39,843
...and he paid cash
out of his left front pocket.

286
00:28:40,009 --> 00:28:43,680
Took his tray of food, sat in a booth
on the east side of the restaurant...

287
00:28:43,847 --> 00:28:46,683
-...and put the knapsack on the floor.
-Where on the floor?

288
00:28:46,850 --> 00:28:48,852
Under his seat, between his legs.

289
00:28:49,436 --> 00:28:51,688
Nobody touched it.

290
00:28:51,855 --> 00:28:55,191
He didn't talk to anybody.
He didn't even look at anybody.

291
00:28:55,358 --> 00:28:59,696
Finished his meal in five minutes tops,
and skedaddled. Didn't leave anything behind.

292
00:28:59,863 --> 00:29:03,742
-And you're sure of that?
-I literally checked the trash can.

293
00:29:03,908 --> 00:29:06,661
There was nothing in there but trash.

294
00:29:09,038 --> 00:29:10,373
So...

295
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:12,584
...what's our next move, huh?

296
00:29:12,751 --> 00:29:14,502
Are we gonna follow this guy?

297
00:29:14,711 --> 00:29:18,798
Because you-- You got some
real James Bond stuff in here.

298
00:29:18,965 --> 00:29:21,134
This car doesn't have an ejector seat,
does it?

299
00:29:21,217 --> 00:29:23,845
I think we're done for today.

300
00:29:24,012 --> 00:29:26,389
-That's it?
-That's it.

301
00:29:28,141 --> 00:29:30,435
I mean, I cleared my morning.

302
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:33,980
What, we're not gonna do, like...?

303
00:29:34,147 --> 00:29:36,024
Tail him to a new location?

304
00:29:36,191 --> 00:29:38,526
Or, I mean,
we gotta sit on him, at least, I--

305
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:41,362
Thanks for your time.

306
00:29:50,580 --> 00:29:51,664
Hey.

307
00:29:51,831 --> 00:29:54,501
Who's got your back, huh?

308
00:29:54,793 --> 00:29:57,003
Me. That's who.

309
00:30:00,006 --> 00:30:02,383
I'll keep that in mind.

310
00:30:13,645 --> 00:30:15,230
[ENGINE STARTS]

311
00:31:29,971 --> 00:31:31,806
[TIRES SQUEAL]

312
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:10,553
[♪♪♪]

313
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,223
<i>♪ When the beef is on</i>
<i>I killed her ♪</i>

314
00:32:14,432 --> 00:32:16,351
<i>♪ Heat so warm</i>
<i>In the pistol's pocket ♪</i>

315
00:32:16,559 --> 00:32:18,436
<i>♪ If we got you in our sight.... ♪♪</i>

316
00:32:58,851 --> 00:33:01,562
Oh, Kim, the conference call
with the Arizona regulator...

317
00:33:01,729 --> 00:33:03,648
...needs to be rescheduled.
Thursday okay?

318
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:06,109
-Oh, yeah. That's fine.
-Okay.

319
00:33:06,901 --> 00:33:10,279
Francesca, have we got any more
of those dietetic butter cookies?

320
00:33:10,446 --> 00:33:12,156
FRANCESCA: I can check.
-Thanks.

321
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:14,409
Welcome, folks.

322
00:33:19,247 --> 00:33:21,124
[PHONE BUZZING]

323
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:28,756
Hey, Ernie. What's up?

324
00:33:32,176 --> 00:33:34,804
Can't you just come inside?

325
00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:50,445
Sorry.

326
00:33:51,779 --> 00:33:53,406
Thanks.

327
00:33:53,698 --> 00:33:55,533
What are we doing out here?

328
00:33:55,992 --> 00:33:59,078
I didn't wanna call you because then
it would leave a phone record.

329
00:34:00,204 --> 00:34:04,208
I was gonna come in, but then
I thought maybe Jimmy shouldn't see me.

330
00:34:04,375 --> 00:34:06,919
-So--
-But you just called me.

331
00:34:07,211 --> 00:34:08,337
Oh.

332
00:34:09,505 --> 00:34:11,424
Guess I screwed up already.

333
00:34:11,591 --> 00:34:14,927
Ernie, screwed what up?
Why don't you want to see Jimmy?

334
00:34:15,094 --> 00:34:17,513
Well, it's just....

335
00:34:17,680 --> 00:34:18,806
[SIGHS]

336
00:34:18,973 --> 00:34:23,061
-I'm not sure how to start.
-You can start by just telling me.

337
00:34:24,645 --> 00:34:25,772
Here's the thing.

338
00:34:25,938 --> 00:34:28,775
I have some information,
but I don't wanna get in trouble.

339
00:34:28,941 --> 00:34:30,693
Trouble with Jimmy?

340
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:31,861
No.

341
00:34:32,028 --> 00:34:33,196
HHM.

342
00:34:33,404 --> 00:34:36,824
I think I'm bound by confidentiality, maybe?

343
00:34:36,991 --> 00:34:39,619
I'm a little hazy on the legal points...

344
00:34:39,786 --> 00:34:43,831
...but if I tell you what I heard
and not Jimmy directly...

345
00:34:43,998 --> 00:34:45,625
...like....

346
00:34:45,833 --> 00:34:47,251
Like we have a buffer...

347
00:34:47,418 --> 00:34:50,213
-...then legally, I'm safe?
-Ernie.

348
00:34:50,379 --> 00:34:53,007
What the hell are you talking about?

349
00:34:53,508 --> 00:34:56,260
I'm-- I'm just worried about Jimmy.

350
00:34:56,469 --> 00:34:58,513
But if I tell him...

351
00:34:59,597 --> 00:35:01,849
...I don't wanna get in trouble too.

352
00:35:02,892 --> 00:35:05,311
Tell Jimmy what?

353
00:35:07,897 --> 00:35:10,316
Lily, I wanna thank you
for bringing your mom down.

354
00:35:10,483 --> 00:35:12,902
It was a delight to meet you, young lady.

355
00:35:13,069 --> 00:35:14,278
Thank you, Jimmy.

356
00:35:14,362 --> 00:35:16,489
Tell your friends,
even if they already have a will...

357
00:35:16,656 --> 00:35:19,158
...it's important to get it updated,
just like you did.

358
00:35:19,325 --> 00:35:21,494
-I'll tell them.
-Now, you remember Francesca.

359
00:35:21,661 --> 00:35:24,997
She'll take care of you the rest of the way.
All right, who's next?

360
00:35:25,164 --> 00:35:28,167
Mr. Witchell. Mr. Witchell, come on down.

361
00:35:28,334 --> 00:35:30,628
You're the next contestant
on <i>The Price is Right.</i>

362
00:35:30,795 --> 00:35:32,338
Jimmy, can I have a moment?

363
00:35:32,505 --> 00:35:34,757
-Excuse me, sir.
FRANCESCA: Looks like everything is....

364
00:35:34,924 --> 00:35:37,176
Apologies, Mr. Witchell.
Just be a second, folks.

365
00:35:37,343 --> 00:35:40,513
FRANCESCA: Oh, my gosh. Have you guys had
the soup over at Cracker Barrel today?

366
00:35:43,683 --> 00:35:45,017
What?

367
00:35:45,309 --> 00:35:46,435
What?

368
00:35:46,602 --> 00:35:49,564
Hey, come on. I got people out there.

369
00:35:49,730 --> 00:35:51,482
-Hello. I can't--
-Give me a dollar.

370
00:35:51,691 --> 00:35:53,484
-Give you a dollar?
-Hand me a dollar.

371
00:35:53,651 --> 00:35:55,194
-Come on.
-Okay.

372
00:35:56,487 --> 00:35:58,489
-All I got's a twenty.
-Fine. Whatever.

373
00:35:58,656 --> 00:35:59,949
All right.

374
00:36:00,116 --> 00:36:01,492
I'm your lawyer now.

375
00:36:01,659 --> 00:36:04,162
If anyone asks me what I know,
we have confidentiality.

376
00:36:04,328 --> 00:36:06,414
-Why do we need confidentiality?
-Jimmy...

377
00:36:06,581 --> 00:36:08,166
...what did you say to Chuck?

378
00:36:09,792 --> 00:36:11,169
Oh.

379
00:36:11,502 --> 00:36:12,962
Here it comes.

380
00:36:13,129 --> 00:36:15,464
Howard, right? Did Howard call?

381
00:36:15,631 --> 00:36:17,592
Relax. No. Let me explain, please.

382
00:36:18,301 --> 00:36:19,468
Please.

383
00:36:19,635 --> 00:36:22,013
Kim, let me set the stage for you, okay?

384
00:36:22,180 --> 00:36:23,931
When I went to Chuck's place last week...

385
00:36:24,015 --> 00:36:26,684
...it was like the inside
of a Jiffy Pop wrapper, all right?

386
00:36:26,893 --> 00:36:28,227
There was Mylar on the walls.

387
00:36:28,394 --> 00:36:30,855
There was Mylar on the ceiling. The ceiling.

388
00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:35,943
He thought his brain wasn't working
because of the Mesa Verde event and so...

389
00:36:36,110 --> 00:36:38,321
...I kind of told him that he was right...

390
00:36:38,487 --> 00:36:40,072
...about everything.

391
00:36:40,239 --> 00:36:41,991
I had to. He-- He--

392
00:36:42,158 --> 00:36:44,493
Kim, he was broken. He was a broken man.

393
00:36:44,660 --> 00:36:48,915
I couldn't leave him in crazy town like that,
so I told him just to make him feel better.

394
00:36:49,123 --> 00:36:51,751
Doesn't matter what he says.
Doesn't matter who he tells.

395
00:36:51,918 --> 00:36:55,046
-Because it's my word against his.
-Jimmy, there's a tape.

396
00:36:56,505 --> 00:36:57,423
What?

397
00:36:57,506 --> 00:37:00,927
There is a tape recording
of you talking to Chuck.

398
00:37:02,053 --> 00:37:03,971
What do you mean? Who?

399
00:37:04,138 --> 00:37:06,432
Who-- He-- He taped me? How?

400
00:37:06,641 --> 00:37:07,767
I don't know how.

401
00:37:07,934 --> 00:37:09,602
He just did, okay?

402
00:37:09,769 --> 00:37:12,230
-Ernie told me.
-Ernie told you?

403
00:37:12,396 --> 00:37:16,192
He said Chuck has a tape recorder wrapped
in a space blanket in his desk drawer.

404
00:37:16,359 --> 00:37:18,194
Ernie was putting new batteries in it...

405
00:37:18,361 --> 00:37:21,113
...and the tape rolled for a few seconds
and he heard you.

406
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:25,076
Your voice saying something
about switching 1261 to 1216.

407
00:37:25,284 --> 00:37:29,247
So clearly, it was this confession of yours.

408
00:37:31,207 --> 00:37:33,209
He taped me?

409
00:37:44,470 --> 00:37:46,055
Yes, Jimmy.

410
00:37:50,559 --> 00:37:52,853
But I'm not sure what he can do with it...

411
00:37:55,147 --> 00:37:57,108
...legally, anyway.

412
00:37:58,985 --> 00:38:01,320
I'm gonna have to do some research.

413
00:38:02,113 --> 00:38:04,740
He made that tape for a reason...

414
00:38:04,907 --> 00:38:07,034
...and we just have to figure out why.

415
00:38:11,455 --> 00:38:12,540
[SIGHS]

416
00:38:14,041 --> 00:38:15,459
Jimmy?

417
00:38:17,795 --> 00:38:20,423
I gotta get back to it.

418
00:38:20,589 --> 00:38:22,216
The lobby's full of clients.

419
00:38:22,383 --> 00:38:23,676
Okay.

420
00:38:25,636 --> 00:38:27,305
We'll figure this out.

421
00:38:28,514 --> 00:38:30,182
Yeah. I know.

422
00:38:33,185 --> 00:38:36,856
Sorry for the delay, everyone.
Mr. Witchell, thank you for your patience.

423
00:38:37,023 --> 00:38:38,316
I see you brought paperwork.

424
00:38:42,028 --> 00:38:43,070
JIMMY:
I gotta say...

425
00:38:43,237 --> 00:38:46,198
...I would never have
thought to collect bottle caps.

426
00:38:46,365 --> 00:38:49,243
Oh, it's a wonderful hobby.

427
00:38:49,410 --> 00:38:52,038
What excites me is the hunt. Heh.

428
00:38:52,204 --> 00:38:54,040
I can imagine.

429
00:38:54,206 --> 00:38:56,375
Pleasure doing business with you, Mr. Tiller.

430
00:38:56,459 --> 00:38:57,877
Why, thank you, Jimmy.

431
00:38:58,044 --> 00:39:01,464
-All right, then. You drive safe.
-Oh, I do.

432
00:39:05,009 --> 00:39:06,761
[SIGHS]

433
00:39:08,429 --> 00:39:11,599
JIMMY: Is that the last one,
or we got any stragglers coming through?

434
00:39:11,766 --> 00:39:12,892
FRANCESCA:
Last one.

435
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:16,604
Well, hey, thanks, Francesca.

436
00:39:16,771 --> 00:39:18,272
You were great today.

437
00:39:18,439 --> 00:39:19,774
You too.

438
00:39:19,940 --> 00:39:21,359
Those folks love you.

439
00:39:25,488 --> 00:39:27,198
Who doesn't?

440
00:39:34,413 --> 00:39:37,041
And that's <i>U.S. v. McKeever?</i>

441
00:39:37,208 --> 00:39:39,710
Right. No, it makes sense.

442
00:39:40,836 --> 00:39:44,382
You were a tremendous help, professor.
Thanks for finding the time.

443
00:39:46,717 --> 00:39:48,219
You too.

444
00:39:48,386 --> 00:39:49,929
Thanks again.

445
00:39:56,977 --> 00:39:58,687
KIM:
<i>Francesca, could you do me a favor?</i>

446
00:39:58,896 --> 00:40:00,773
Can you go through the Mesa Verde files...

447
00:40:00,856 --> 00:40:03,359
...and pull all the ones labeled
"CRA evaluations"...

448
00:40:03,526 --> 00:40:06,028
...and sort them by date?
I need to have the most recent.

449
00:40:06,195 --> 00:40:08,364
-Absolutely.
-Thank you.

450
00:40:08,531 --> 00:40:11,117
-I'll join you in a minute.
-Okay.

451
00:40:13,661 --> 00:40:15,079
So...

452
00:40:15,663 --> 00:40:18,290
...just got off the phone
with my old Crim-Pro professor.

453
00:40:18,457 --> 00:40:19,792
Oh, yeah? What'd he say?

454
00:40:19,959 --> 00:40:21,001
Well, as we know...

455
00:40:21,168 --> 00:40:25,005
...New Mexico is one-party consent,
so Chuck had a right to make the recording.

456
00:40:25,172 --> 00:40:28,551
But you went to him worried
for his mental health.

457
00:40:29,218 --> 00:40:31,887
You said the things you did
to make him feel better...

458
00:40:32,054 --> 00:40:35,349
...which mitigates the admission of guilt,
at the very least.

459
00:40:36,767 --> 00:40:38,727
We can poke holes in the custody...

460
00:40:38,894 --> 00:40:41,605
...throw doubt the voice
on the tape is even yours.

461
00:40:41,772 --> 00:40:45,568
Even failing that, its probative value
doesn't outweigh how prejudicial it is.

462
00:40:45,734 --> 00:40:49,029
I think we can get the whole thing
bounced under 403.

463
00:40:49,196 --> 00:40:51,449
Probably get it excluded outright.

464
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:54,910
So then...

465
00:40:55,786 --> 00:40:58,205
...outside the courts, what can he do?

466
00:40:59,415 --> 00:41:02,251
Play the tape for Kevin at Mesa Verde?

467
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:05,379
He hasn't up to now.
I'd have heard something, for sure.

468
00:41:05,546 --> 00:41:09,425
Know what? Don't think he will. Howard
won't let him near Mesa Verde with that tape.

469
00:41:09,592 --> 00:41:13,012
Howard knows it would make HHM look terrible.

470
00:41:19,727 --> 00:41:22,563
If Chuck has a plan for this tape,
I don't know what it is.

471
00:41:23,397 --> 00:41:27,610
At this point, all we can do is wait
for his move, then act accordingly.

472
00:41:32,031 --> 00:41:33,824
All right, then.

473
00:41:34,867 --> 00:41:36,368
Thanks.

474
00:41:36,994 --> 00:41:38,370
Sure.

475
00:41:40,206 --> 00:41:42,333
Oh, hey, what do you think? Um....

476
00:41:42,500 --> 00:41:46,337
It's Etude in Blue over Daydream Harvest.

477
00:41:46,504 --> 00:41:50,007
I wanted it to look like morning
over the Sandias.

478
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:53,552
-I like it. It looks nice.
-It doesn't look like a stock-market crash?

479
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:57,765
No. It doesn't look like
a stock-market crash.

480
00:41:57,932 --> 00:41:59,767
It's nice.

481
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:01,185
Thanks.

482
00:42:07,316 --> 00:42:08,484
You okay?

483
00:42:11,862 --> 00:42:13,781
Kim, I'm good.

484
00:42:41,684 --> 00:42:42,977
[♪♪♪]

485
00:44:00,596 --> 00:44:02,097
[DOOR OPENS]

486
00:44:37,424 --> 00:44:38,842
[PHONE RINGING]

487
00:44:55,609 --> 00:44:57,194
Yeah.

488
00:46:13,353 --> 00:46:14,813
Oof!

489
00:46:21,069 --> 00:46:22,613
[CHIMING]

490
00:46:22,779 --> 00:46:24,740
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

491
00:46:41,632 --> 00:46:43,091
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

492
00:46:54,102 --> 00:46:57,231
-Howard, what are you doing here?
-Chuck, do you have a second?

493
00:46:57,397 --> 00:46:59,650
Did you-- You parked over on the next block?

494
00:46:59,816 --> 00:47:02,069
-Oh, yeah. Way over.
-Yeah.

495
00:47:02,277 --> 00:47:03,946
Uh, phone. Keys.

496
00:47:05,531 --> 00:47:07,658
Hey, you have to hide them.

497
00:47:20,170 --> 00:47:21,380
Everything okay, sir?

498
00:47:21,547 --> 00:47:22,965
Yes, thank you, David.

499
00:47:23,131 --> 00:47:25,050
-Give us a moment.
-Yes, sir.

500
00:47:27,803 --> 00:47:30,264
-What's up?
-Chuck...

501
00:47:30,848 --> 00:47:32,891
...this has been going on
for eight days now...

502
00:47:32,975 --> 00:47:35,352
...and really, no indication
that it's going to work.

503
00:47:35,519 --> 00:47:37,104
It will work.

504
00:47:37,312 --> 00:47:39,314
I think I've been very patient...

505
00:47:39,565 --> 00:47:44,695
...but the cost of these
around-the-clock private investigators...

506
00:47:44,861 --> 00:47:46,989
-...is really starting to add up.
-Howard.

507
00:47:47,155 --> 00:47:48,782
This is our duty.

508
00:47:48,949 --> 00:47:50,826
As officers of the court...

509
00:47:50,993 --> 00:47:53,412
-...we have an ethical obligation to--
HOWARD: Yes.

510
00:47:53,579 --> 00:47:55,414
My brother broke the law.

511
00:47:55,581 --> 00:47:59,418
-We can't just sit back and do nothing.
-I'm not talking about doing nothing.

512
00:47:59,585 --> 00:48:01,587
I just want to...

513
00:48:01,753 --> 00:48:03,088
...free up our minds...

514
00:48:03,255 --> 00:48:06,967
...and be open
to alternate strategies, please.

515
00:48:08,135 --> 00:48:09,636
Meet me halfway here.

516
00:48:09,803 --> 00:48:11,680
[SIGHS]

517
00:48:13,348 --> 00:48:15,309
I suppose--

518
00:48:15,767 --> 00:48:19,354
I suppose we could limit
the investigators to just nighttime hours.

519
00:48:19,563 --> 00:48:21,106
-Nighttime.
-Yes.

520
00:48:21,273 --> 00:48:24,484
Jimmy will most likely break in
while he thinks I'm sleeping.

521
00:48:24,651 --> 00:48:28,363
I mean, I wouldn't put anything past him.
It just makes the most sense...

522
00:48:28,530 --> 00:48:30,657
...he'll try to steal the tape
under darkness.

523
00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:32,409
You really think he's going to do that?

524
00:48:32,576 --> 00:48:34,453
I do, indeed.

525
00:48:34,620 --> 00:48:36,246
How can you be so sure?

526
00:48:37,289 --> 00:48:38,707
Howard...

527
00:48:39,666 --> 00:48:41,668
...I know my brother.

528
00:48:42,002 --> 00:48:43,086
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

529
00:48:43,295 --> 00:48:44,588
JIMMY:
Chuck!

530
00:48:46,089 --> 00:48:47,549
Chuck.

531
00:48:48,842 --> 00:48:50,218
Open the damn door, Chuck!

532
00:48:51,053 --> 00:48:53,180
Open the door, damn it. Open it. Chuck.

533
00:48:53,347 --> 00:48:55,390
-Jimmy, go away.
JIMMY: Open the door! Open it now!

534
00:48:55,557 --> 00:48:58,685
-I'm not opening the door. I am not op--
-I swear to God, Chuck.

535
00:48:58,894 --> 00:49:00,354
Jimmy. Jimmy.

536
00:49:00,729 --> 00:49:01,855
You taped me?

537
00:49:02,022 --> 00:49:03,440
-You asshole.
-Jimmy.

538
00:49:03,607 --> 00:49:05,776
You pulled that heartstrings con job on me?

539
00:49:05,984 --> 00:49:08,362
You piece of shit!

540
00:49:08,737 --> 00:49:12,532
[IMITATING CHUCK] "Oh, my brain used to work.
I'm sick. I don't know what to do."

541
00:49:12,699 --> 00:49:14,451
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Asshole!

542
00:49:14,618 --> 00:49:16,119
No wonder Rebecca left you.

543
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:19,623
What took her so long?

544
00:49:22,125 --> 00:49:23,877
There it is!

545
00:49:27,923 --> 00:49:31,009
Here we go. Here we go.

546
00:49:31,218 --> 00:49:33,095
Here we go.

547
00:49:33,720 --> 00:49:35,305
[GRUNTING]

548
00:49:39,434 --> 00:49:41,019
Is this it?

549
00:49:41,186 --> 00:49:44,731
Is this it? Is this it? Huh?

550
00:49:44,940 --> 00:49:47,359
For this, you destroyed our family?

551
00:49:47,567 --> 00:49:49,403
You happy now? For what?

552
00:49:49,569 --> 00:49:51,613
For nothing!

553
00:49:53,448 --> 00:49:55,575
Is that all there is, Chuck?

554
00:49:56,201 --> 00:50:00,038
It's all the-- All there is?
Or did you make copies? Huh, Chuck?

555
00:50:00,247 --> 00:50:03,375
You tell me, or I'll burn this
whole goddamn house to the ground.

556
00:50:03,583 --> 00:50:04,876
Jimmy. Jimmy.

557
00:50:05,335 --> 00:50:07,045
That's enough.

558
00:50:08,130 --> 00:50:09,381
You need to step away.

559
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:12,968
Howard...

560
00:50:14,052 --> 00:50:17,180
-...you were a witness to what happened here?
-I was.

561
00:50:17,347 --> 00:50:18,557
And you?

562
00:50:18,724 --> 00:50:20,559
I'm a witness.

563
00:50:42,914 --> 00:50:44,916
[♪♪♪]
